squads.name: Asajj L
squads.description: Infinite revives potential with Nightsister Zombie, damage through protection, healing, and cleansing.
squads.generalStrategy: Avoid Nightsister Zombie's constant taunting [dispel / buff immunity] or work around it [strong AoEs].  Having healers or high health steal is effective.  You want to kill Old Daka 3 times (to stop the auto revives and her revives), kill Mother Talzin, then kill Asajj Ventress (because she's more powerful now due to the deaths).  If no Enfys Nest, then kill whichever 4th character is used, then finally Nightsister Zombie.  If 4th is Nightsister Acolyte, you definitely want a dispeller or you can easily get caught between her stealth and Nightsister Zombie's taunt.  If Enfys Nest, save her for last.

squads.name: Bossk L 1.0
squads.description: Bossk's leadership gives all Bounty Hunters extra protection, tenacity, and defense (while at full health). They recover health and protection when an enemy suffers or resists a debuff. When they fulfill their contract, all Bounty Hunters gain +50 speed for the rest of the battle on top of their own payouts.
squads.generalStrategy:
Bossk's contract is exploitable. They need to damage the weakest enemy 10 times, so you can slow this down using taunters.

You'll want to deal with Bossk by having someone that can either dispel his taunt or apply ability block/buff immunity before he can taunt.

You'll need good single target damage because this team will heal frequently and the Fetts will revive, so you'll need to kill them twice.

If Greef is part of the team, need to account for his initial Stealth and the mass debuff cleanse, tenacity up and 50% TM gain on his third special, which can neutralize RJT led teams.

Kill order: Boba Fett, Jango Fett, and other Bounty Hunters, Bossk, then Dengar last (because he'll probably be in stealth until the end).

squads.name: Carth L
squads.description: Lot of damage over time and nice bonus synergy shared between each other [offense, tenacity, assists and defense/crit avoidance, protection recovery].
squads.generalStrategy: Stop the damage over time from spreading, dispel Zaalbar frequently from his taunt to focus on attackers/support first.  Can't rely on debuffs/have really high potency (Bastila Shan (Fallen) and Carth will have 80% tenacity, rest 30%).  Bypass the crit avoidance (Zaalbar+Mission have 55% Crit Avoidance, rest 30%).  Use their slow speed against them with turn meter gain, you should have speed advantage.  Kill order: Canderous Ordo, Carth Onasi or Mission Vao.

squads.name: Ewoks
squads.description: Crit team with lot of assists, buffs, and usually daze and revive. High TM gain from Chief Chirpa's zeta lead.

squads.name: Jawas
squads.description: High damage if using IG-86 or IG-88,  turn meter gain, crit chance/damage gain, and healing from Jawa Engineer.
squads.generalStrategy: Daze and AoE, having crit avoidance.  Kill Jawa Engineer first, then IG-88, then the rest.

squads.name: CLS L 2.0
squads.description:
Primary members are Threepio & Chewie, Chewbacca, and Han Solo.

Rebel squad with high Counter Attack chance, high Crit Chance and Crit Damage, frequent assists, deal a lot of debuffs, start the battle with crippling attacks, and require a specific kill order.
squads.generalStrategy:
- avoid using AoE attacks
- follow the kill order:
  - Threepio & Chewie
  - Chewbacca
  - Han Solo
  - Commander Luke Skywalker

squads.name: DR L 3.0
squads.description: Sith Empire are a debuff heavy squad with powerful Turn Meter manipulation mechanics, perks when defeating an enemy leader, and they gradually become more powerful throughout the battle.
squads.generalStrategy: You'll want a squad that can withstand the Turn Meter loss, frequent debuffs, and double Taunt.  Based on your counter squad, you'll either want to defeat Bastila Shan (Fallen) or HK-47 first.

squads.name: DR L 2.0
squads.description: Sith Empire are a debuff heavy squad with powerful Turn Meter manipulation mechanics, perks when defeating an enemy leader, and they gradually become more powerful throughout the battle.
squads.generalStrategy:
You'll want a squad that can withstand the Turn Meter loss and frequent debuffs.  Based on your counter squad, you'll either want to defeat Bastila Shan (Fallen) or HK-47 first.

Kill order:  Bastila Shan (Fallen) or HK-47, Darth Revan, Darth Malak, Sith Marauder

Traya L 2.0
squads.description: Primary members are Darth Nihilus, Darth Sion, and Darth Vader.

squads.name: Finn L 2.0
squads.description: Primary members are Poe Dameron, Veteran Smuggler Chewbacca, and Veteran Smuggler Han Solo.

squads.name: Finn L 1.0
squads.description: Primary members are Resistance Hero Poe, Veteran Smuggler Chewbacca, and Veteran Smuggler Han Solo.

squads.name: GG L w/ Nute
squads.description: Separatist debuff team, specifically focusing on the use of Target Lock.  Nute Gunray is substituted in for Droideka to further weaken the enemy and strengthen his allies with his Extortion mechanic.
squads.generalStrategy:
- use a squad that can easily resist or cleanse debuffs
- target B2 Super Battle Droid first
- target Grievous second, if possible

squads.name: GG L (Sep Droids)
squads.description: Separatist debuff team, specifically focusing on the use of Target Lock.
squads.generalStrategy:
- use a squad that can easily resist or cleanse debuffs
- target B2 Super Battle Droid first
- target Grievous second, if possible

squads.name: GS L
squads.description: General Skywalker's leadership uses the Advance and Cover mechanics.  In Advance, if GAS has 501st allies, they can't lose health and he gets an undispellable taunt until his protection is dropped to 0%.  With 501st allies present and GAS's protection at 0%, then he goes into Cover where he can't be targeted and is immune to damage and status effects.
squads.generalStrategy:
Ideally, you want to knock down General Skywalker by dropping his protection to 0%, then take out the clones before he returns from Cover.

Try to defeat CT-5555 "Fives" first. Or else, he will sacrifice himself with his Tactical Awareness zeta, which will buff the remaining 501st Clone Troopers and may make it impossible to defeat the remaining allies before GAS returns from his first round of Cover. Next take out CT-7567 "Rex" before he can get a big hit with Aerial Advantage., CT-24-0408 "Echo", the last ally, then General Skywalker last.

Kill order: Fives, Rex, Echo, last ally, GAS

squads.name: Geos
squads.description: Separatist squad that relies heavily on assists and can deal substantial damage to a single target.  They have increased Max Health and Protection, Health Steal, and they equalize their Health and Protection across the team whenever an enemy uses an ability.
squads.generalStrategy:
- use a counter that can
  - handle high amount of assists
  - handle heavy single-target damage
  - handle getting around a persistent Taunt
  - can put out enough damage to work through extra Health and Protection, Health Steal, and Health and Protection recovery and equalization
- target Geonosian Brood Alpha first
- target Geonosian Spy second

squads.name: Phoenix 1.0 w/ Ezra
squads.description: High synergy team with a lot of counter attacking, dispelling (or loving the debuffs), and HP + protection recovery. Be careful with G12 zeta Phoenix, use equally geared zeta'd teams.
squads.generalStrategy: Avoid getting countered [daze or attacking from stealth/assists]. Deal good damage in a single turn that surpasses their heals (calling assist/simply high damage/high turn meter gain).  There's no point in debuffing because of Kanan's unique (besides Daze/Stun).  Focus on one character at a time to remove the unique ability they are sharing with the team.  Killing Chopper removes health/protection regeneration.  Killing Ezra removes stacking offense up.  Killing Sabine removes increased crit chance and crit damage.  Killing Kanan removes counter chance and health regen on debuff.  Killing Zeb removes protection regen.  Killing Hera removes turn meter gain on using special ability.

squads.name: Jango L 1.0
squads.description: Primary members are Bossk, Greef Karga, and The Mandalorian.  Jango Fett's leadership gives Scoundrel allies +30 speed, punishes your team for putting debuffs them by lowering your potency and tenacity, and prevents turn meter for anyone with the Burning effect. When they fulfill their contract, all Bounty Hunters gain offense on top of their own payouts.

squads.name: JMLS L 1.0
squads.description: Primary members are Jedi Knight Luke Skywalker, Obi-Wan Kenobi (Old Ben), and Shaak Ti.

squads.name: Rogue One
squads.description: Team with heal, protection recovery (if zJyn Erso), lot of debuffs, and Chaze (Chirrut Îmwe and Baze Malbus) make this a formidable team.
squads.generalStrategy: Killing Chirrut Îmwe will stop the heal over time [or stop with Buff Immunity using Jedi Knight Anakin].  Need to dispel Baze's taunt while removing Chirrut's protection and focusing on Chirrut hard. [Veers Mass attack] Also try to avoid the debuffs from Cassian, K-2SO and Baze. [tenacity up/ high tenacity] another option is simply anti-rebel power [Wampa, DK, DT] or let them stack their heal over time buffs then use Boba's Execute.

squads.name: KRU L 1.0
squads.description: Primary members are First Order Executioner, First Order Officer, and Kylo Ren.  Synergy team with counter attacking, dispelling (or loving the debuffs), healing + protection recovery, and high crit damage.
squads.generalStrategy: Avoid getting countered frequently (daze/attack from stealth and assists), dont rely on debuffs, and deal damage that surpass their heals with single big-hitters or turn meter gains.  Kill order: First Order Executioner, First Order Officer, First Order TIE Pilot.

squads.name: MM L 1.0
squads.description: Primary members are Biggs and Wedge

squads.description: Infinite revives potential with Nightsister Zombie, damage through protection, healing, and cleansing.

squads.name: GR 1.0 w/ Barriss
squads.description: Primary members are Ahsoka Tano, Jedi Knight Anakin, and General Kenobi.  Super tanky team, immunity to debuffs (with many options to dispel), protection-up spamming, damage based on % of target's health, and benefits when enemies attack out of turn.
squads.generalStrategy: Buff immunities (+Isolate + Fracture + zeta Imperial Probe Droid) to deny buffing and stacking of protection-up and bonus % damage.  Kill order: Padmé Amidala, Jedi Knight Anakin.

squads.name: Qi'ra L 1.0
squads.description: Heals, revives, protection regeneration, and lot of taunts.  This is a very hard team to beat.
squads.generalStrategy: Requires dispelling, healing immunity, lot of turn meter gain, and AoE attackers.  Kill Vandor Chewbacca first and don't let him revive his allies.  Keep Zaalbar and L3-37 shutdown by dispelling them.  Kill order: Vandor Chewbacca, Qi'ra/Mission Vao/Young Han Solo/Young Lando Calrissian, L3-37, Enfys Nest, Zaalbar.

squads.description: Primary members are Amilyn Holdo, Resistance Hero Finn, and Resistance Hero Poe

squads.description: Primary members are Count Dooku, Darth Sidious, and Sith Empire Trooper

squads.description: Primary members are Darth Nihilus, Darth Sion, and Darth Traya

squads.name: Traya L 3v3 w/ Nihilus and Sion
Enfys Nest (solo)
squads.description: Enfys Nest (solo) excels against teams that have a high attack rate but low power output.  She has a high counter chance and ignores taunts.  She gains stacking crit chance and protection every time she is damaged before her turn (these reset at the end of her turn).  And throughout the encounter, she also gains crit damage and health steal whenever an enemy loses a buff or debuff.
squads.generalStrategy:
You want teams/characters with Daze, Stun, Stealth, Thermal Detonators, and/or possibly Tenacity Down. You don't want to use teams that reduce her turn meter, as it'll delay her from shedding the undispellable Protection Up on her turn, which could cause a time-out situation.

The ideal strategy for most teams is to either apply debuffs or use a basic attack (tryin not to reduce turn meter or prompt assists) until she takes a turn, then the next time you deal damage should be a high-damage single target attack. It may be beneficial to save abilities that don't deal damage for this moment, so you don't waste your first damage-dealing attack after her turn with a low-damage attack that she could easily heal from.

squads.name: JTR L 4.0
squads.description: Turn meter gain, high damage and assists from BB-8, annoying foresights and recoveries from Rey (Jedi Training).  Crit team built on exposes for the turn meter.
squads.generalStrategy: Stopping BB-8 and Rey (Jedi Training) is key. The damage is from crits and exposes, so crit avoidance works well and reduced damage from exposes as well.  Hard to daze them because of foresights, so need to stop the turn meter train in other ways (disabling BB-8, crit avoidance) or exploit the high amount of turns (Plague).  Kill order: BB-8/Resistance Trooper, Rey (Scavenger), Rey (Jedi Training).

squads.description: Primary members are Sith Trooper, General Hux, and Kylo Ren (Unmasked)
